						               													<description>Medieval Magic Market is a card game in which you will assume the role of an adventurous newcomer to the great Flanaghar Market. Your goal is to trade with the loot achieved in your adventures. You must use object cards, action, along with your character's ability to be the one who gets the most gold coins (represented on the object cards) at the end of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During each round, players draw 2 cards and can play any number of Object cards, but only one of Action cards, if an Event card is drawn at the time of drawing cards, it is resolved immediately.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object cards have different values of gold coins, but it is necessary to discard some of these during the game in order to make moves that grant more Object cards, hence more gold coins. So you should save some of these to score at the end of the game. The Action cards modify the dynamics of the player who plays them in favor of him. Event cards must be played before the start of the turn, they never remain in the player's hand, they modify the game of all the players involved. The players also have a character card with a respective ability in favor of these, In addition there is a card from The Market has Closed that is put into play after the third round and being stolen ends the game, then the points represented in gold coins that each player has in his hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
